! file cufft.h brief Public header file for the NVIDIA CUDA FFT library (CUFFT)

CUFFT API function return valuesCUFFT defines and supports the following data types cufftReal is a single-precision, floating-point real data type. cufftDoubleReal is a double-precision, real data type.cufftComplex is a single-precision, floating-point complex data type that consists of interleaved real and imaginary components. cufftDoubleComplex is the double-precision equivalent.CUFFT transform directionsCUFFT supports the following transform typesCUFFT supports the following data layoutsstructure definition used by the shim between old and new APIs cufftHandle is a handle type used to store and access CUFFT plans.utility functions

Imports

cuComplex, library_types

Types

cudaStream_t = pointer
cufftCompatibility {.size: 4.} = enum
  CUFFT_COMPATIBILITY_FFTW_PADDING = 1 ## The default value
cufftComplex = cuComplex
cufftDoubleComplex = cuDoubleComplex
cufftDoubleReal = cdouble
cufftHandle = cint
cufftReal = cfloat
cufftResult {.size: 4.} = enum
  CUFFT_SUCCESS = 0, CUFFT_INVALID_PLAN = 1, CUFFT_ALLOC_FAILED = 2,
  CUFFT_INVALID_TYPE = 3, CUFFT_INVALID_VALUE = 4, CUFFT_INTERNAL_ERROR = 5,
  CUFFT_EXEC_FAILED = 6, CUFFT_SETUP_FAILED = 7, CUFFT_INVALID_SIZE = 8,
  CUFFT_UNALIGNED_DATA = 9, CUFFT_INCOMPLETE_PARAMETER_LIST = 10,
  CUFFT_INVALID_DEVICE = 11, CUFFT_PARSE_ERROR = 12, CUFFT_NO_WORKSPACE = 13,
  CUFFT_NOT_IMPLEMENTED = 14, CUFFT_LICENSE_ERROR = 15, CUFFT_NOT_SUPPORTED = 16
cufftType {.size: 4.} = enum
  CUFFT_C2C = 41,           ## Complex to Complex, interleaved
  CUFFT_R2C = 42,           ## Real to Complex (interleaved)
  CUFFT_C2R = 44,           ## Complex (interleaved) to Real
  CUFFT_Z2Z = 105,          ## Double-Complex to Double-Complex
  CUFFT_D2Z = 106,          ## Double to Double-Complex
  CUFFT_Z2D = 108            ## Double-Complex to Double

CUFFT_FORWARD = -1
CUFFT_INVERSE = 1
CUFFT_VER_BUILD = 95
CUFFT_VER_MAJOR = 11
CUFFT_VER_MINOR = 0

CUFFT_VERSION = 11001
MAX_CUFFT_ERROR = 0x00000011
MAX_SHIM_RANK = 3
